            <h1>International relations</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/internasjonalt_150x113.jpg" alt="Hands holding a globe" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Norwegian foreign policy aims to safeguard Norwegian interests and values in a rapidly changing world, while at the same time helping to further the international common good and contribute to making the world a better organised place.</p>
            <img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/internasjonalt_150x113.jpg" alt="Hands holding a globe" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>As the expert ministry, <em>the Ministry of Foreign Affairs</em> is both a preparatory and an executive body in connection with foreign policy matters, economic foreign policy issues and aid-related matters. The Ministry has two ministers, the Minister of Foreign Affairs and the Minister of International Development. <br />On this page you will find general information and documents relating to international relations. You can explore this topic in more detail by using the menu on the right.<br /></p></div>
